the creature is not wearing armor, roll on the major injury chart and the creature is disfigured. While disfigured the creature has disadvantage on all Charisma ability checks except Charisma (Intimidation). Being disfigured can be removed with the spell greater restoration.","img":"modules/critical-fumble/icons/acid.svg","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
